This paper deals with structured prediction in natural language processing, which is a common topic in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of retrieve-and-edit based approaches also involves machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dynamic programming, which is a common technique in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of sequence labeling in computer vision, which is relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of nearest neighbors, which is a common technique in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
